========================================
The ACTPR Benchmarking System
========================================

`Anonymized Github Link <https://anonymous.4open.science/r/19c83e2b-0176-4ae2-b231-b260a74794e3/>`__

ACTPR Model
----------------

The ACTPR model is the core of our benchmarking system. It defines five evaluation metrics for the FL systems: Accuracy, Communication, Time consumption, Privacy and Robustness.

The Benchmarking System
-----------------------------------------------

.. raw:: html

   <html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
   <head></head>
   <body><center><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="50%" style="margin: 0 auto;"></center></body>
   </html>

We publish an easy-to-use and lightweight benchmarking system for federated learning (FL). The above figure shows the framework of the system, and it contains the following three steps:

- **Step 1:** Distribute the data to all clients, where different strategies can be applied to generate IID or non-IID data.
- **Step 2:** Provide the training scripts and distribute the codes to all the clients.
- **Step 3:** Training the model. The ACTPR evaluation model will run automatically in this step. 

The above three steps will run automatically by the sysetm, and we only need to provide necessary configs. Mode detaies about the config can be found in the **Project overview** and **Contents**.

We used the docker container technology to simulate the server and clients. The isolation between different containers guarantees that our simulation can reflect the real-world application. **All the benchmark system is open-sourced, and five benchmark FL datasets are included in the system.** Thus researches can implement their new idea and evaluate with ACTPR model very quickly.
